
To install terraform on a Windows/Linux machine and build, apply, and destroy EC2 instance
over AWS using Terraform.(CODE)
# Configure the AWS Provider
provider "aws" {
  access_key = ""
  secret_key = ""
  region     = "us-east-1"
}

# Launch an EC2 instance
resource "aws_instance" "terraformUser" {
  ami           = ""  # Replace with a region-specific valid AMI
  instance_type = "t3.micro"
  count = 3

  tags = {
Name = "praj"
}
}

Q5) To deploy Docker and build, apply, and destroy docker image using Terraform.
terraform{
required_providers{
docker={
source="kreuzwerker/docker"
version="2.14.0"
}
}
}
provider "docker"{
host="npipe:////.//pipe//docker_engine"
}
resource "docker_image" "redis" {
name="redis:latest"
}
